    "description": "Join the Navkar Corporation Asia Pacific Associates family as a Logistics Manager in Raipur. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Navkar Corporation Asia Pacific Associates:\nNavkar Corporation Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage relationships with third-party logistics providers\n• Prepare MIS reports on delivery performance and SLA adherence\n• Track shipments in real-time and resolve delivery exceptions\n• Manage reverse logistics and return merchandise authorization\n• Implement warehouse management systems (WMS) and track KPIs\n• Ensure proper handling, packaging, and labeling of goods\n• Implement cost-saving initiatives in transportation and warehousing\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Post Graduate Diploma in relevant field\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Route Optimization\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in Customs Clearance\n• Proficiency in Inventory Management\n• Proficiency in Cold Chain Logistics\n• Proficiency in Reverse Logistics\n• Proficiency in Vendor Management\n• Proficiency in KPI Monitoring\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Learning & development budget\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Raipur, Chhattisgarh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Navkar Corporation Asia Pacific Associates!",
